Fairmont Marina Residences Project includes a world-class luxurious addition by the National Investment Corporation that offers a collection of 1 bedroom, 2 bedroom, 2 bedroom, and 3 bedroom hotels as well as apartments. The project is located in Abu Dhabi and the designed twin-tower development is said to be linked by the Gold Lounge that is located on the 37th and 38th floor. These two floors overlook the Abu Dhabi skylines as well as the open sea. The location of the Fairmont Marina Residences Project is strategic as it has major access through the major roadways in the country that lead to Sheikh Zayed Bin Sultan Street and Corniche Street. This will offer free access to just about anywhere, including the hotel. Also Read: Jabal Hafit Gardens Project in Abu Dhabi: 146 Gardens Delivered The Fairmont Marina Residences Project aims to provide to both local and international guests and residents direct access to the beach, breathtaking views of the Abu Dhabi Skylines as well as the ocean. ome of the hotels feature indirect access to the beach, an infinity pool, a fitness center, leisure areas and parks, a study center, and a gymnasium. There will also be a basketball court, jogging trails, cycling traits, a mosque, spa and sauna, a hospital, a community hall, a shopping mall, a tennis court, and a running track. The hotel will also offer transport convenience to all its guests as it will be 37 minutes from the Abu Dhabi International airport, 24 minutes for the Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, 9 minutes from Emirates Palance, 25 minutes for Louvre Abu Dhabi, and lastly, 36 minutes from Yas Mall.